          </physDesc>
          <history>
            <summary>
              <p>A note in the main body of Arch. Seld. B.24 refers to James IV as
                king, meaning production of the manuscript must have been begun
                sometime after 1488 (Boffey et al. 1997: 4). The appearance of the
                date 1592 on fol. 231v, among the spare leaves towards the end of
                the manuscript, implies that it was complete by this date, although
                this is uncertain.</p>
              <p>It is thought that it was produced for the Sinclair family in either
                Edinburgh or Roslin (Boffey et al. 1997: 11).</p>
              <p>The manuscript was bequethed to the Bodleian Library as part of the
                collection of John Selden (1584–1654) (Brown 1899: 93). How it came
                to be in his collection is not known but the window between his
                collecting activities and the window in which the manuscript was
                composed is sufficiently narrow for there not to have been a
                significant intervening history.</p>
            </summary>
          </history>
